are the following steps correct:   1.	Take three DuPont wires crimped with male connectors at both ends;
2.	Prepare an RS232 to RS485 adapter (for illustration only, use the appropriate device you have);
3.	Identify the screen printing on the adapter and the serial port of the device. For RS232 mode, connect RXD to TXD, TXD to RXD, and GND to GND; for RS485 mode, connect 485 A to 485 A, and 485 B to 485 B;
4.	Unscrew the 3-pin connector that is included in the packing list and the RS232 to RS485 adapter;
5.	Insert one end of the DuPont wires to the RS232 to RS485 adapter and the other end to the 3-pin connector following the pinout described in the prior step, then tighten the screws;
